  After two more bottles, and some pizza close to a week old the shadow of a future hangover had put its feet up on the couch.  The drive only had several folders of pictures, one shaky video, and a few cryptic text files.  Almost all the photos looked like late-night partying.
  It wasn’t as diverse of a mix as the cheap strip joint.  Their clothes looked trashy, the kind of trashy that comes with a price tag.  The guys with them looked like wasted office workers, some older &amp; some younger.  And then there was the kicker.
