  She’d taken a selfie while sitting on some guy&#039;s lap.
  I couldn&#039;t have described her fur pattern properly after work-induced braindeath and a few beers, but she was one of the wolf looking girls.  Youngish, dark-eyed and a row of earrings &amp; piercings in one ear, almost black hair against fur that alternated dark brown and glossy black.  If she ever took out all the extra piercings in that ear and put on some clothes she&#039;d look like just another plain college girl.
  The beer had gone warm and tasteless, and I cursed the goddess or saint of sticking your nose in things before grabbing another beer and making the call without a coin flip.  I went back through the CD case.  Her name was Deedee, at least when working the club.

